parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the transmission dislodges from the fifth gear
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the gear shifts suddenly
the vehicle stops moving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CV joint can cause the vehicle to become immobile, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The CV axle comes out of the trans axle
the clip comes out of the CV joint
the vehicle becomes immobile
the vehicle makes a loud popping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The rear axle fails
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle becomes immobile.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the clutch fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifting system can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear doesn't shift until reaching a certain speed
the gear shifts suddenly
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the aluminum rim can cause the wheel to bend or crack, leading to loss of air pressure, loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The rim bends or cracks
especially on the inboard side
causing air to escape
the wheel to vibrate
or the vehicle to pull to one side
and in severe cases
the wheel can fall off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sale of defective used tires can lead to serious safety issues, including tire blowouts, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can result in property damage, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Tires appear to be in good condition but are actually defective
tires become flat or blow out suddenly
tires have visible signs of damage or wear
such as melted or flimsy material on the inside of the tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire blowouts can lead to road debris, which can cause hazardous road conditions, accidents, and property damage.
symptoms: Tire debris is left on the road
vehicles encounter tire debris while driving
vehicles are damaged or involved in accidents due to tire debris.
